in javascript how do you save to and read back from localstorage
To save a value in local storage, use the `localStorage.setItem()` method like this: 
```javascript
// Save data into local storage
var myValue = "Hello World!";
localStorage.setItem("myKey", JSON.stringify(myValue)); // Convert to string and store as key-value pair in local storage
console.log('Data saved!');
``` 
To read a value from local storage, use the `localStorage.getItem()` method like this: 
```javascript
// Read data from local storage
var myValue = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem("myKey")); // Convert string back to object and assign it to variable
console.log('Data read!');
```
